<section class="positioning">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sec-head reveal"><span class="sec-index">01 / Positioning</span><span class="sec-rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="reveal" style="margin-bottom: 64px;">We collapse the distance between intent and outcome.</h2>
    <div class="contrast-grid">
      <div class="card glow-card reveal">
        <p class="card-kicker">The old world</p>
        <p>You buy software. You hire people to operate it. The people are the intelligence layer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card glow-card reveal">
        <p class="card-kicker">The transition world</p>
        <p>You buy AI tools. You still hire people to manage them. Nothing fundamentally changes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card emph glow-card reveal">
        <p class="card-kicker">What we build</p>
        <p>An intelligent execution layer. It does the work. Your team steers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="diagram reveal" id="diagram">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 820 140" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="A line connecting intent to outcome with agent nodes along the path">
        <text x="20" y="76" class="node-label">INTENT</text>
        <circle cx="130" cy="70" r="5" fill="#FFFFFF" />
        <path id="flowline" d="M 135 70 H 675" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.5)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" />
        <polygon id="traveler" points="133,65 145,70 133,75" fill="#FFFFFF" />
        <circle cx="680" cy="70" r="5" fill="#FFFFFF" />
        <text x="706" y="76" class="node-label">OUTCOME</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
